# Shipment Execution Model

## Overview

Shipment execution is the stage of wholesale operations where validated and allocated orders are physically prepared and dispatched to customers.

This stage connects warehouse operations, logistics coordination, and transportation partners to ensure orders are delivered according to customer expectations.

---

## Key Shipment Execution Steps

Shipment execution generally includes the following stages:

1. Order release to warehouse  
2. Picking and packing of products  
3. Label generation and carton preparation  
4. Carrier booking or scheduling  
5. Shipment dispatch  

Each step must align with retailer compliance requirements.

---

## Warehouse Fulfillment Process

Warehouse teams typically perform the following activities:

• picking ordered products  
• verifying product quantities  
• packing cartons or pallets  
• applying shipping labels  
• preparing shipment documentation  

Accuracy during fulfillment prevents downstream shipment issues.

---

## Transportation Coordination

Logistics teams coordinate transportation by:

• selecting approved carriers  
• scheduling pickup appointments  
• confirming routing guide compliance  
• generating bills of lading  
• monitoring shipment tracking

Carrier coordination ensures shipments move efficiently through the transportation network.

---

## Shipment Visibility

Operations teams track shipment status through:

• carrier tracking systems  
• warehouse management systems  
• retailer portals  
• transportation management systems

Shipment visibility allows operations teams to respond quickly if issues occur.

---

## Operational Risks

Shipment execution issues may include:

• incorrect labeling  
• shipment delays  
• incorrect carrier usage  
• routing guide violations  
• incomplete shipment documentation

Proper process controls reduce these risks.

---

## Final Note

Shipment execution is where operational planning becomes physical product movement. Clear coordination between warehouse teams, logistics staff, and carriers ensures shipments reach customers on time and in compliance with retailer requirements.
